  "text": "Two days before the collection of peritoneal macrophages mice were intraperitoneally (i.p.) injected with 1 ml of 10% Sephadex G-25 (Pharmacia, Uppsala, Sweden) and peritoneal exudate cells were collected on the selected days after cessation of the irradiations (in each case the cells were collected and pooled from at least five mice), resuspended in CM and incubated on glass Petri dishes for 2 h in SC. The glass-adherent cells with morphological features of a typical macrophage were then harvested and resuspended in CM [CITATION_1] ).",
